# Cell Splitting Calculator

## Description
This program helps calculate how to split cells in cell culture.

In the lab, when we passage cells, we usually take a fraction of the culture (for example 1:10) and add fresh medium to reach the same final volume. This script calculates how much volume of cells to take and how much medium to add.

## How to use
Run the program and enter:
- The total volume of the cell culture (in mL)
- The split ratio (for example, enter 10 for a 1:10 split)

## What the program does
The program calculates:
- Volume of cells to take
- Volume of fresh medium to add
- Final volume

## Example

Input:
Total volume: 10 mL
Split ratio: 10

Output:
Take 1.00 mL of cells
Add 9.00 mL of medium
Final volume: 10.00 mL

  
